<title>JAPAN: Japan March domestic vehicle sales up 12.4% yr/yr.</title>
<headline>Japan March domestic vehicle sales up 12.4% yr/yr.</headline>
<dateline>TOKYO 1997-04-01</dateline>
<text>
<p>Japan's domestic vehicle sales in March rose 12.4 percent from a year earlier to 830,864 units, the Japan Automobile Dealers' Association (JADA) said on Tuesday.</p>
<p>It was the seventh successive gain on a year-on-year basis and the highest level ever for any March, surpassing the previous record of 788,880 set in March 1990.</p>
<p>Japan's domestic vehicle sales in the year to March 1997 rose 7.6 percent from the previous year to 5.56 million units, the third successive year of gains.  </p>
<p>The following is a breakdown of 1996/97 sales (with percentage changes from a year earlier):</p>
<p> Total cars		3,876,670  up   9.7 percent</p>
<p> - Cars over 2001 cc     940,930  up   4.6 percent</p>
<p> - Cars under 2000 cc  2,935,740  up  11.5 percent</p>
<p> Total trucks	    1,667,606  up   2.9 percent</p>
<p> - Heavy trucks	    175,204  up   2.2 percent</p>
<p> - Light trucks	  1,492,402  up   3.0 percent</p>
<p> Buses			  17,330  dowm 1.6 percent</p>
<p>The 1996/97 sales included 437,883 imported vehicles, up 8.8 percent from the year before.</p>
<p>Vehicle sales in 1996/97 by Japanese makers were as follows (with percentage changes from a year earlier):</p>
<p> Toyota Motor     2,191,282  up   8.5 percent</p>
<p> Nissan Motor     1,111,636	   unchanged</p>
<p> Honda Motor	  574,943  up  39.8 percent</p>
<p> Mitsubishi Motors  478,102  down 2.9 percent</p>
<p> Mazda Motor	  300,813  up   0.8 percent</p>
<p> Fuji Heavy	   146,311  up   7.0 percent</p>
<p> Isuzu Motors	 140,770  down 0.6 percent</p>
<p> Suzuki Motor	  67,489  up  11.4 percent</p>
<p> Hino Motors	   49,329  up   6.2 percent</p>
<p> Nissan Diesel	 33,784  up   3.7 percent</p>
<p> Daihatsu Motor	29,264  up  71.6 percent</p>
<p>The figures announced on Tuesday are preliminary. Final figures will be announced on April 4, but these rarely differ from preliminary figures, a JADA official said.</p>
<p>The March sales breakdown was as follows (with percentage changes from a year earlier):</p>
<p> Total cars		585,446  up  15.4 percent</p>
<p> - Cars over 2001 cc   135,158  up  19.2 percent</p>
<p> - Cars under 2000 cc  450,288  up  14.4 percent</p>
<p> Trucks		    241,560  up   5.8 percent</p>
<p> - Heavy trucks	   32,403  up  15.1 percent</p>
<p> - Light trucks	  209,157  up   4.5 percent</p>
<p> Buses			 3,858  up   6.6 percent</p>
<p>The March sales included 57,837 imported vehicles, up 12.7 percent from the year before.</p>
